<specimenCode box="[782,941,645,671]" collectionCode="MNRJ" country="Brazil" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/zi1i-a0b5" name="Museu Nacional/Universidade Federal de Rio de Janeiro" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">MNRJ 12010</specimenCode>
)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,333,741,767]" box="[151,333,741,767]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,333,741,767]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Redescription.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,813,1705]" box="[151,1034,813,840]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,318,813,840]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Size and form</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[332,432,814,840]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">holotype</typeStatus>
<specimenCount box="[439,462,814,840]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
). Body length = 42 and wide = 
<quantity box="[817,885,814,840]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" unit="mm" value="7.0">7 mm</quantity>
. TL/GW = 6.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,813,1705]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,849,875]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Coloration</emphasis>
(long preserved in 70% ethanol). Head, prozonite, metazonite and telson brown, antennomeres, paranota and posterior region of the epiproct orange, legs yellow (
<figureCitation box="[891,1014,886,912]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[201,1386,181,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-22@16.[201,1386,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 9. Somatic features of Haematotropis disjuncta Golovatch, Hoffman &amp; Spelda, 2004 (IEPA). A. Head and body rings 1–5, dorsal view, holotype ♂ (IEPA). B. Head and body rings 1–5, lateral view, holotype ♂ (IEPA). C. Body rings 9–11, dorsal view, holotype ♂ (IEPA). D. Body rings 18–20, dorsal view, holotype ♂ (IEPA). E. Habitus, lateral view, paratype ♀ (IEPA). Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653729" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653729/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 9A–E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,813,1705]" box="[199,960,922,948]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,270,922,948]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Head.</emphasis>
Dorsal surface smooth and shiny, without microgranulations.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,813,1705]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,282,958,984]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Trunk.</emphasis>
Collum 
<quantity box="[383,450,958,984]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[523,590,958,984]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" unit="mm" value="7.0">7 mm</quantity>
wide; dorsal surface of all rings smooth and shiny, without microgranulations; posterolateral margins slightly concave (
<figureCitation box="[669,788,994,1020]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[201,1386,181,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-22@16.[201,1386,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 9. Somatic features of Haematotropis disjuncta Golovatch, Hoffman &amp; Spelda, 2004 (IEPA). A. Head and body rings 1–5, dorsal view, holotype ♂ (IEPA). B. Head and body rings 1–5, lateral view, holotype ♂ (IEPA). C. Body rings 9–11, dorsal view, holotype ♂ (IEPA). D. Body rings 18–20, dorsal view, holotype ♂ (IEPA). E. Habitus, lateral view, paratype ♀ (IEPA). Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653729" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653729/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 9A, B</figureCitation>
). Rings 2–19: prozonite and metazonite smooth and shiny, without microgranulation in dorsal region of all rings. Anterolateral teeth on paranota of rings 2–4 (
<figureCitation box="[1249,1339,1030,1056]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1714,1738]" captionTargetBox="[281,1307,181,1690]" captionTargetId="figure-22@8.[281,1307,181,1690]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2. General somatic features of Haematotropis Jeekel, 2000. A. H. jurutiensis sp. nov., non-type ♂ (MPEG), body ring 7, ventral view. B. H. jurutiensis sp. nov., non-type ♂ (MPEG), body ring 9 (highlighting the microgranulations), ventral view. C. H. jurutiensis sp. nov., non-type ♂ (MPEG), body ring 7, red arrow indicates the wrinkles close to paranota, ventral view. D. H. jurutiensis sp. nov., non-type ♂ (MPEG), body ring 8, red arrow indicates rounded projections on ventral surfaces, ventral view. E. H. jurutiensis sp. nov., non-type ♂ (MPEG), metazonite of body ring 8, red arrow indicates the microgranulations on anterior and posterior margins, dorsal view. F. H. megalcensis sp. nov. non-type ♂ (IBSP), body ring 10, red arrow indicates the microgranulations on anterior and posterior margins, ventral view. G. H. callipa, holotype ♂ (MfN), head and body rings 1–4, red arrow indicates a depression on collum or anterolateral teeth, dorsalateral view. Scale bars: 300 μm (A, E), 200 μm (C, D, F), 100 μm (B), 1 mm (G)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653710" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653710/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 2G</figureCitation>
). Lateral margins of ring 2 not projected posteriad (
<figureCitation box="[629,752,1066,1092]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[201,1386,181,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-22@16.[201,1386,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 9. Somatic features of Haematotropis disjuncta Golovatch, Hoffman &amp; Spelda, 2004 (IEPA). A. Head and body rings 1–5, dorsal view, holotype ♂ (IEPA). B. Head and body rings 1–5, lateral view, holotype ♂ (IEPA). C. Body rings 9–11, dorsal view, holotype ♂ (IEPA). D. Body rings 18–20, dorsal view, holotype ♂ (IEPA). E. Habitus, lateral view, paratype ♀ (IEPA). Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653729" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653729/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 9A, B</figureCitation>
). Gonopodal aperture elliptical, approximately 
<quantity box="[1288,1374,1066,1093]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
wide and 
<quantity box="[199,285,1102,1129]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
long at midpoints. Telson (
<figureCitation box="[590,678,1102,1128]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[201,1386,181,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-22@16.[201,1386,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 9. Somatic features of Haematotropis disjuncta Golovatch, Hoffman &amp; Spelda, 2004 (IEPA). A. Head and body rings 1–5, dorsal view, holotype ♂ (IEPA). B. Head and body rings 1–5, lateral view, holotype ♂ (IEPA). C. Body rings 9–11, dorsal view, holotype ♂ (IEPA). D. Body rings 18–20, dorsal view, holotype ♂ (IEPA). E. Habitus, lateral view, paratype ♀ (IEPA). Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653729" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653729/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 9D</figureCitation>
) smooth and shiny, without microgranulations.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,813,1705]" box="[199,788,1138,1164]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,262,1138,1164]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Legs.</emphasis>
Smooth and shiny, without microgranulations.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,813,1705]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1173,1199]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Gonopods.</emphasis>
Right gonopod structure as follows: coxa with lateral swelling at midlength (
<figureCitation box="[1223,1328,1174,1200]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[203,1384,181,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-19@17.[203,1384,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Right gonopod of Haematotropis disjuncta Golovatch, Hoffman &amp; Spelda, 2004, holotype ♂ (IEPA). A. Mesal view. B. Dorsal view. C. Lateral view. D. Ventral view. Yellow scale indicates when VP1 exceeds the width of ventral region of acropodite. Abbreviations: Ac = acropodite; Ca = cannula; Cx = coxa; DP = Distal Process 1; LP1 = Lateral Process 1; Pf = Prefemur; S = Solenomere; Sg = Spermatic groove; Ste = setae; VP1 = Ventral Process 1. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653731" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653731/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 10C</figureCitation>
); acropodite elongated, about four times as long as prefemur; median region expanded, cup-shaped in ventral view, with a concavity and cavity (
<figureCitation box="[421,527,1246,1272]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[203,1384,181,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-19@17.[203,1384,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Right gonopod of Haematotropis disjuncta Golovatch, Hoffman &amp; Spelda, 2004, holotype ♂ (IEPA). A. Mesal view. B. Dorsal view. C. Lateral view. D. Ventral view. Yellow scale indicates when VP1 exceeds the width of ventral region of acropodite. Abbreviations: Ac = acropodite; Ca = cannula; Cx = coxa; DP = Distal Process 1; LP1 = Lateral Process 1; Pf = Prefemur; S = Solenomere; Sg = Spermatic groove; Ste = setae; VP1 = Ventral Process 1. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653731" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653731/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 10D</figureCitation>
); distal region of acropodite slightly sinuous, not bifurcate, curved ventrally at a 70° angle (
<figureCitation box="[277,417,1282,1308]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[203,1384,181,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-19@17.[203,1384,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Right gonopod of Haematotropis disjuncta Golovatch, Hoffman &amp; Spelda, 2004, holotype ♂ (IEPA). A. Mesal view. B. Dorsal view. C. Lateral view. D. Ventral view. Yellow scale indicates when VP1 exceeds the width of ventral region of acropodite. Abbreviations: Ac = acropodite; Ca = cannula; Cx = coxa; DP = Distal Process 1; LP1 = Lateral Process 1; Pf = Prefemur; S = Solenomere; Sg = Spermatic groove; Ste = setae; VP1 = Ventral Process 1. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653731" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653731/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 10A–C</figureCitation>
); VP1 emarginated on posterior region, evident, exceeding the width of ventral region of acropodite, in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[468,609,1318,1344]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[203,1384,181,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-19@17.[203,1384,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Right gonopod of Haematotropis disjuncta Golovatch, Hoffman &amp; Spelda, 2004, holotype ♂ (IEPA). A. Mesal view. B. Dorsal view. C. Lateral view. D. Ventral view. Yellow scale indicates when VP1 exceeds the width of ventral region of acropodite. Abbreviations: Ac = acropodite; Ca = cannula; Cx = coxa; DP = Distal Process 1; LP1 = Lateral Process 1; Pf = Prefemur; S = Solenomere; Sg = Spermatic groove; Ste = setae; VP1 = Ventral Process 1. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653731" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653731/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 10A, C</figureCitation>
); VP2 absent; LP1 long and tapered, strongly curved apically, projected towards the mesal region of gonopod (
<figureCitation box="[574,711,1354,1380]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[203,1384,181,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-19@17.[203,1384,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Right gonopod of Haematotropis disjuncta Golovatch, Hoffman &amp; Spelda, 2004, holotype ♂ (IEPA). A. Mesal view. B. Dorsal view. C. Lateral view. D. Ventral view. Yellow scale indicates when VP1 exceeds the width of ventral region of acropodite. Abbreviations: Ac = acropodite; Ca = cannula; Cx = coxa; DP = Distal Process 1; LP1 = Lateral Process 1; Pf = Prefemur; S = Solenomere; Sg = Spermatic groove; Ste = setae; VP1 = Ventral Process 1. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653731" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653731/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 10A–D</figureCitation>
), LP2 and LP3 absent; DP tapered, sinuous and projected towards the gonopod apical region (
<figureCitation box="[460,598,1390,1416]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[203,1384,181,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-19@17.[203,1384,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Right gonopod of Haematotropis disjuncta Golovatch, Hoffman &amp; Spelda, 2004, holotype ♂ (IEPA). A. Mesal view. B. Dorsal view. C. Lateral view. D. Ventral view. Yellow scale indicates when VP1 exceeds the width of ventral region of acropodite. Abbreviations: Ac = acropodite; Ca = cannula; Cx = coxa; DP = Distal Process 1; LP1 = Lateral Process 1; Pf = Prefemur; S = Solenomere; Sg = Spermatic groove; Ste = setae; VP1 = Ventral Process 1. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653731" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653731/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 10A–C</figureCitation>
). Opening of solenomere located at distal end of acropodite (
<figureCitation box="[1286,1424,1390,1416]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[203,1384,181,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-19@17.[203,1384,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Right gonopod of Haematotropis disjuncta Golovatch, Hoffman &amp; Spelda, 2004, holotype ♂ (IEPA). A. Mesal view. B. Dorsal view. C. Lateral view. D. Ventral view. Yellow scale indicates when VP1 exceeds the width of ventral region of acropodite. Abbreviations: Ac = acropodite; Ca = cannula; Cx = coxa; DP = Distal Process 1; LP1 = Lateral Process 1; Pf = Prefemur; S = Solenomere; Sg = Spermatic groove; Ste = setae; VP1 = Ventral Process 1. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653731" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653731/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 10A–C</figureCitation>
). Solenomere with long, acuminated apex, projected towards LP1 (
<figureCitation box="[884,1022,1426,1452]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[203,1384,181,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-19@17.[203,1384,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Right gonopod of Haematotropis disjuncta Golovatch, Hoffman &amp; Spelda, 2004, holotype ♂ (IEPA). A. Mesal view. B. Dorsal view. C. Lateral view. D. Ventral view. Yellow scale indicates when VP1 exceeds the width of ventral region of acropodite. Abbreviations: Ac = acropodite; Ca = cannula; Cx = coxa; DP = Distal Process 1; LP1 = Lateral Process 1; Pf = Prefemur; S = Solenomere; Sg = Spermatic groove; Ste = setae; VP1 = Ventral Process 1. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653731" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653731/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 10A–C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,813,1705]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1462,1488]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Golovatch, Hoffman &amp; Spelda" authorityYear="2004" box="[321,457,1462,1488]" class="Diplopoda" family="Aphelidesmidae" genus="Haematotropis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="disjuncta">
<emphasis box="[321,341,1463,1488]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[354,457,1462,1488]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">disjuncta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="De &amp; Bueno-Villegas &amp; Rafael, 2021" authorityName="De &amp; Bueno-Villegas &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2021" box="[653,834,1462,1488]" class="Diplopoda" family="Aphelidesmidae" genus="Haematotropis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="disjunctoides" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[653,673,1463,1488]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[686,834,1462,1488]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">disjunctoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[839,927,1462,1488]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[839,927,1462,1488]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in the conformation of both gonopods and the presence of DP (
<figureCitation box="[338,480,1498,1524]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[203,1384,181,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-19@17.[203,1384,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Right gonopod of Haematotropis disjuncta Golovatch, Hoffman &amp; Spelda, 2004, holotype ♂ (IEPA). A. Mesal view. B. Dorsal view. C. Lateral view. D. Ventral view. Yellow scale indicates when VP1 exceeds the width of ventral region of acropodite. Abbreviations: Ac = acropodite; Ca = cannula; Cx = coxa; DP = Distal Process 1; LP1 = Lateral Process 1; Pf = Prefemur; S = Solenomere; Sg = Spermatic groove; Ste = setae; VP1 = Ventral Process 1. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653731" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653731/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Figs 10A–D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[492,579,1498,1525]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,705,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-243@37.[151,1435,705,1913]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 26. Somatic features of Haematotropis disjunctoides sp. nov., holotype ♂ (MPEG). A. Head and body rings 1–4, dorsal view. B. Head and body rings 1–6, dorsolateral view. C. Body rings 11–14, dorsal view. D. Body rings 18–20, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653789" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653789/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">26A–D</figureCitation>
). However, the apex of DP not being bifurcate and not surpassing the dorsal distal region of the acropodite (
<figureCitation box="[513,652,1534,1560]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[203,1384,181,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-19@17.[203,1384,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Right gonopod of Haematotropis disjuncta Golovatch, Hoffman &amp; Spelda, 2004, holotype ♂ (IEPA). A. Mesal view. B. Dorsal view. C. Lateral view. D. Ventral view. Yellow scale indicates when VP1 exceeds the width of ventral region of acropodite. Abbreviations: Ac = acropodite; Ca = cannula; Cx = coxa; DP = Distal Process 1; LP1 = Lateral Process 1; Pf = Prefemur; S = Solenomere; Sg = Spermatic groove; Ste = setae; VP1 = Ventral Process 1. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653731" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653731/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 10A–D</figureCitation>
) distinguishes 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Golovatch, Hoffman &amp; Spelda" authorityYear="2004" box="[824,963,1534,1560]" class="Diplopoda" family="Aphelidesmidae" genus="Haematotropis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="disjuncta">
<emphasis box="[824,844,1535,1560]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[860,963,1534,1560]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">disjuncta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName authority="De &amp; Bueno-Villegas &amp; Rafael, 2021" authorityName="De &amp; Bueno-Villegas &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2021" box="[1036,1220,1534,1560]" class="Diplopoda" family="Aphelidesmidae" genus="Haematotropis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="disjunctoides" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1036,1056,1535,1560]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1072,1220,1534,1560]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">disjunctoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1229,1321,1534,1560]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1229,1321,1534,1560]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, in which DP bifurcates irregularly and extends beyond the dorsal distal region of the acropodite (
<figureCitation box="[1141,1279,1570,1596]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[193,1394,181,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-22@38.[193,1394,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 27. Right gonopod of Haematotropis disjunctoides sp. nov., holotype ♂ (MPEG). A. Mesal view. B. Dorsal view. C. Lateral view. D. Ventral view. Yellow scale indicates when VP1 exceeds the width of ventral region of acropodite. Abbreviations: Ac = acropodite; Ca = cannula; Cx = coxa; DP = Distal Process 1; LP1 = Lateral Process 1; Pf = Prefemur; Sg = spermatic groove; S = Solenomere; Ste = setae; VP1 = Ventral Process 1. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5653791" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5653791/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 27A–C</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Golovatch, Hoffman &amp; Spelda" authorityYear="2004" box="[1299,1437,1570,1596]" class="Diplopoda" family="Aphelidesmidae" genus="Haematotropis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="disjuncta">
<emphasis box="[1299,1319,1571,1596]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1334,1437,1570,1596]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">disjuncta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs mainly on the north shore of the Amazon River (
